Claims CLAIMS: 1. A shell portion for a floatation system, the shell portion comprising: a peripheral connection portion configured to engage a corresponding peripheral connection portion of a second shell portion; and a cavity defined by an internal surface extending from the peripheral connection portion; wherein the shell portion is configured to cooperate with the second shell portion such that the cavity forms part of a sealed chamber in use. 2. The shell portion according to claim 1, wherein the shell portion is a nestable shell portion. 3. The shell portion according to claims 1 or 2, wherein the connection portion comprises a plurality of apertures configured to receive a bayonet pin. 4. The shell portion according to any preceding claim, wherein the peripheral connection portion is a flange. 5. The shell portion according to any preceding claim, wherein the peripheral connection portion comprises a cooperative sealing feature. 6. The shell portion according to claim 5, wherein the cooperative sealing feature is a projection or a recess. 7. The shell portion according to any preceding claim, wherein one or more support projections extend into the cavity. 8. The shell portion of any preceding claim, wherein the shell portion comprises a trench for receipt of cables therein. 9. A floatation assembly for a floatation system, the floatation assembly comprising: a first shell portion according to any preceding claim; and a second shell portion according any preceding claim; 

 wherein the peripheral connection portions of the first and second shell portions engage one another, the respective cavities defining the sealed chamber. 10. A walkway shell portion assembly for a floatation system, the assembly comprising: a shell portion according to any one of claims 1 to 8; and one or more lids; the one or more lids engaging the shell portion to define a walkway surface. 11. A walkway floatation assembly for a floatation system, the walkway assembly comprising: the shell portion of any one of claims 1 to 8; and the walkway shell portion assembly of claim 10; wherein the peripheral connection portions of the shell portions engage one another, the respective cavities thereby defining the sealed chamber. 12. The shell portion according to any one of claims 1 to 8, further comprising a solar panel mount. 13. A solar panel shell portion assembly for a floatation system, the assembly comprising: the shell portion according to claim 12, and one or more clamp arrangements engaged with the solar panel mount, the one or more clamp arrangements being configured to provide a solar panel mounting platform. 14. A solar panel floatation assembly for a floatation system, the assembly comprising: the shell portion according to any one of claims 1 to 8; the solar panel shell portion assembly according to claim 13; and wherein the peripheral connection portions of the shell portions engage one another, the respective cavities thereby defining the sealed chamber. 15. The solar panel floatation assembly according to claim 14, further comprising one or more solar panels mounted to the solar panel mounting platform. 16. A bayonet pin for a floatation system, the bayonet pin comprising: a head; and a shank extending from the head along an axis, the shank comprising one or more lugs extending outwardly therefrom; and an integral locking pin, the locking pin being receivable by the head to limit rotation of the bayonet pin in use. 17. The bayonet pin according to claim 16, wherein the one or more lugs comprises a pair of diametrically opposed lugs which extend radially from an end of the shank. 18. The bayonet pin according to either of claims 16 or 17, wherein the locking pin is flexibly tethered to the head. 19. A connection plate for connecting a plurality of floatation assemblies separate to the connection plate, the connection plate comprising a plurality of apertures configured to receive a bayonet pin. 20. The connection plate according to claim 19, wherein the connection plate comprises an aperture in each one of four corner regions. 21. The connection plate according to any one of claims 16 to 20, wherein the apertures are recessed into the connection plate to define a ledge. 22. A floatation system comprising: a first floatation assembly according to claim 9 when dependent, directly or indirectly, upon claim 3; a second floatation assembly according to claim 9 when dependent, directly or indirectly, upon claim 3; first and second bayonet pins according to any one of claims 16 to 18; and the connection plate according to any one of claims 19 to 21 ; wherein a first aperture of the connection plate is aligned with an aperture of the first floatation assembly, and the first bayonet pin is received through the apertures to connect the connection plate to the first floatation assembly; and 

 wherein a second aperture of the connection plate is aligned with an aperture of the second floatation assembly, and the second bayonet pin is received through the apertures to connect the connection plate to the second floatation assembly, the first and second floatation assemblies thereby being connected to one another via the connection plate. 23. A solar floatation system comprising: a walkway floatation assembly according to claim 11 when dependent, directly or indirectly, upon claim 3; a solar panel floatation assembly according to claims 14 or 15 when dependent, directly or indirectly, upon claim 3; first and second bayonet pins according to any one of claims 16 to 18; and the connection plate according to any one of claims 19 to 21 ; wherein a first aperture of the connection plate is aligned with an aperture of the first floatation assembly, and the first bayonet pin is received through the apertures to connect the connection plate to the first floatation assembly; and wherein a second aperture of the connection plate is aligned with an aperture of the second floatation assembly, and the second bayonet pin is received through the apertures to connect the connection plate to the second floatation assembly, the first and second floatation assemblies thereby being connected to one another via the connection plate. 24. A method of assembling a floatation system, the method comprising: i) aligning an aperture of a first floatation assembly according to claim 9 when dependent, directly or indirectly, upon claim 3, with a first aperture of a connection plate according to any one of claims 19 to 21 ; iii) inserting a first bayonet pin, according to any one of claims 16 to 18, through the first aperture of the connection plate and the aligned aperture of the first floatation assembly, in a first rotational position, and then rotating the first bayonet pin about the axis to a second rotational position, the first floatation assembly thereby being connected to the connection plate. 25. The method according to claim 24, further comprising the step of inserting the locking pin into the head of the first bayonet pin to constrain rotation of the first bayonet pin. 26. The method according to claims 24 or 25, wherein step i) further comprises placing the connection plate over an offset section of an upper connection portion of the first floatation assembly such that the offset section is engaged by a corresponding recess in the connection plate, the engagement thereby aligning the apertures in the floatation assembly and connection plate relative to one another.
